{
  "stem": "13258.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But you have full economical rights, which means you have to get paid the same as Soviet citizens are getting paid for their jobs, with the provision that 10% of your earnings are going to be deducted to keep for the [INAUDIBLE], for apparently, he didn't explain us, for supervising us, for taking care of us.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The next morning, the foreman came.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], Citizen [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And some of us got assigned to a sawmill, and some got assigned to the forest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My father and I, we got two axes and a saw and a bottle of kerosene and a rag and-- on a stick.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we were led to the forest, and we were shown how to cut down trees.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And if, say, a bottle of kerosene was needed because in summertime, the resin sticks to the saw, so you moisten the saw a little bit with resin, and we were told what to do and how many cubic meters of what we had to produce every day.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first of all, we were so good at lumberjacking that from that job we got transferred, because we would have gone through the forest in no time.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And we got assigned to sawmill, which was a little better.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I got assigned to various jobs, and subsequently my father to other jobs too.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we stayed there until almost September of 1941.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When the war had broken out with-- between Russia and Germany-- first of all, all mail stopped.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From that day on-- until then, we had been getting mail.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We even got a parcel from my mother from Poland, from German-occupied Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the day the war started, no mail from the West was arriving anymore.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "From East, we got some mail later.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
